<!--This is a code I made to show how I create a border and what the different settings will do.-->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
body 	{background-color: Black;}
h1   	{color: White;}
h1	{align: center;}
p    	{color: red;}
</style>
</head>


<body>
<h1 align="center" style="border:1px; border-style:solid; border-color:red; padding: .2em;" > Border is 1px. Border is solid. Padding is .2 . Centered. </h1>
<h1 align="center" style="border:2px; border-style:double; border-color:red; padding: .1em;" > Border is 2px. Border is double. Padding is .1 . Centered. </h1>
<h1 align="left" style="border:5px; border-style:dotted; border-color:red; padding: .5em;" > Border is 5px. Border is dotted. Padding is .5 . Left. </h1>
<h1 align="right" style="border:10px; border-style:dashed; border-color:red; padding: 1em;" > Border is 10px. Border is dashed. Padding is 1 . Right. </h1>
<h1 align="justify" style="border:15px; border-style:double; border-color:red; padding: 3em;" > Border is 15px. Border is double. Padding is 3 . Justify. </h1>
<h1 align="center" style="border:20px; border-style:groove; border-color:red; padding: 5em;" > Border is 20px. Border is groove. Padding is 5 . Centered. </h1>
<h1 align="left" style="border:25px; border-style:ridge; border-color:red; padding: 1em;" > Border is 25px. Border is ridge. Padding is 1 . Left. </h1>
<p align="center">This assigns attributs in head style.</p>


</body>
</html>
